
data_binary_position.RDS

RDS collecting in a unique, organized, dataframe the various quantities extracted from the .mat file.
(It combines all the .RDS files named "M3424F_xxx.RDS")

'data.frame':	10870 obs. of  330 variables:
 $ pos_binary  : variable that encodes the binary position of the mouse (inner circle/outer ring) at each time point. Encoded as {1,2}
 $ pos1        : x-coordinate of the mouse location at each time point
 $ pos2        : y-coordinate of the mouse location at each time point
 $ time_pos    : time (ms) of the mouse position 
 $ time_calcium: time (ms) of the calcium recording
 $ X1          : fluorescence level of neuron 1 at each time point 
 $ X2          : fluorescence level of neuron 2 at each time point 
 ...            ...
 $ X325        : fluorescence level of neuron 325 at each time point 

 
